<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Developer-ID (DEVID) entitlements for the macOS app. Selected ONLY by
  scripts/build_signed_app.sh when DEVID_BUILD_FLAG=1; the Mac App Store
  archive (CLI Pulse Bar/scripts/build-appstore.sh via xcodebuild) keeps
  using the sandboxed CLI_Pulse_Bar.entitlements — do NOT point the Xcode
  target at this file.

  Difference vs the MAS file: the App Sandbox is REMOVED. The in-app
  terminal is gated on `MASSandboxGate.canHostInAppTerminal = !isSandboxed`,
  so the sandboxed MAS-shaped signing hid it on every shipped build. The
  PTY itself runs in the unsandboxed LaunchAgent helper (cli_pulse_helper),
  so dropping the parent's sandbox is a distribution choice, not a technical
  requirement — but it is the only drag-and-drop .app/DMG path that un-hides
  the terminal (a sandboxed app cannot register an unsandboxed LaunchAgent
  via SMAppService — the W1-B SMAppService catch-22).

  KEPT: application-groups + keychain-access-groups so the shared
  Group Container UDS/token path (LocalSessionControlClient) and the
  prompt-free keychain reads keep working. On an unsandboxed Developer-ID
  binary these are honoured via the team signature (KHMK6Q3L3K) without a
  provisioning profile — exactly how the LaunchAgent helper already works.
  build_signed_app.sh expands `$(AppIdentifierPrefix)` to the team prefix at
  sign time (codesign does NOT expand the macro itself).

  DROPPED (sandbox-only, meaningless / ignored once unsandboxed):
    com.apple.security.app-sandbox
    com.apple.security.files.bookmarks.app-scope
    com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>group.yyh.CLI-Pulse</string>
	</array>
	<key>keychain-access-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>$(AppIdentifierPrefix)group.yyh.CLI-Pulse</string>
	</array>
	<key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
